snippet.textDisplay: Thank you for the honesty with Subaru’s! I bought a 1998 legacy wagon ej25 with 130,000 miles, previous owner did head gaskets, I had to do head gaskets a second time,  auto trans failed, cam slipped and wrecked a head, and at the same time my buddy’s girlfriends outback had its THIRD head gasket job done with only 170,000 miles on it. Another friend’s 2010 WRX had the whole engine replaced at 15,000 miles. My dad’s friend collects $500 2.2 legacies with blown head gaskets for parts to keep his “good legacy” running. Subaru reliability is s myth, they’re just easy to work on so home mechanics keep them running.
